Training Center  Four 1st Class cadets completed a special warfare or special operations screener this summer in preparation for entry into SEAL or Explosive Ordnance Disposal   EOD   technician training  Twelve Marine option 1st Class cadets completed Marine Corps Officer Candidates School in Quantico  Va  earning the opportunity to accept commissions as Marine officers upon graduation  Eighteen 3rd Class cadets completed Career Orientation and Training for Midshipmen   CORTRAMID  These cadets spent one week each with aviation  submarine  surface  and Marine Corps units  experiencing training  including aerobatics in a T 34 and marksmanship training at Camp Lejeune  Info Courtesy of Naval ROTC IR   Sept  2014 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 